race.comment: GOOD'N'YOU (2) started a dominant fav on debut after the three good trials with a handy third over 1200m at this track. Improvement is anticipated and gets the dream run again. BUGATTE (3) resumes with the two trials after finishing an even sixth over 1200m at Warwick Farm last October. Blinkers go on and shapes as a solid top-three contender. LUCKY ME (11) just missed the frame on debut then finished 11th in a 1300m contest at Kembla Grange a month ago. Gear change and worth keeping safe. CHISPA (8) on debut. Hasn't shown much at the trials, but has the benefit of a good draw. Watch for any market confidence.
